  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On page one of this manuscript, there is a letter by Parker Pillsbury to William Lloyd Garrison. Parker Pillsbury sends a gift of a half barrel of flour. The letter is signed Parker and Sarah H. Pillsbury.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On pages 2 through 3 of this manuscript, there is a draft of a letter by William Lloyd Garrison to Wendell Phillips in Jan. 1851. Garrison gives the amount of his debt for his household and other expenditures. He emphasizes his wife&apos;s economy and his own frugality.</subfield>
